Get the Panang curry, mild+! We order it all the time and it is absolutely delicious. A little spicy even with it being mild but still so good! We just moved here and we are already frequent customers. Crab Rangoon is great too!

I go to this great spot  a lot! This is the best place to eat.  I visit this spot many times. The cooking is very tasty, the staff is welcoming and the prices are good. I enjoy eating in this place for a nice meal.

I love Pho’s! It’s my go-to for Thai food or when I get home late and want to have something delivered. The food I’ve ordered has always been delicious, spicy, and hot, and the delivery is usually quite fast. I’ve ordered from GrubHub and have started ordering directly from the restaurant, and all of my experiences have been awesome.

We usually order through GrubHub, but yesterday we were around the area and decided to go in person for some Thai teas and some food. The Thai teas here are delicious and the food is pretty good for the price. Sure, it's not mind-blowing good, but the prices are great and the sizes are huge, you can easily split one meal between two people. Great late night place to get a bite, too. This is definitely our to-go when we don't feel like cooking, but want some real food
Super slow delivery.  They never seem to answer their phone.  I won’t be ordering here again.
Wow... walking distance from Loyola... and GREAT tasting food!
I get to eat here a lot since I work nearby. I must say the service is always fantastic and they keep the spot neat regularly. Prices are convenient and they serve generous portions.

Ordered a lunch special and they individually charged me for everything doubling the price. When I asked about it, she just said “sorry” and made me pay. When I got home, they ordered me an extra appetizer that I didn’t order. Quantities were all wrong for orders. Just don’t come here I guess
They are only open until 10 not midnight
Nice good food

TL;DR - Excellent Customer Service and Tasty Food  I ordered from Grubhub and the delivery driver gave my food to someone in the lobby who claimed to be me (my neighbor stole my food). I contacted Grubhub to help and they were useless, so I reached out to the store directly as it was only 10 mins before they closed. The staff member who answered was apologetic and had my order remade and redelivered meaning the staff stayed at least 30 mins late to correct the mistake. I am appreciative of their commitment to their customers. Thanks!  Plus the food was delicious.

The customer service is really weak. The fried rice and pad see wee taste like trash. They put soya sauce too much. I recommend people who have high blood pressure to not go there, their food are all salty.

First off this is not authentic Thai/Vietnamese cuisine. The Red Curry Chicken had more carrots in it than anything else. The veggies were frozen and processed. The Tom Yum soup tastes like water and tomatoes. No flavor at all!!! They give you 3 shrimp in a small order. I have never ate Tom Yum soup with absolutely no flavor. The spiciness overwhelms the non existant flavor and I like spicy! Then to top it all off the food made me sick!! If you love yourself and great food DO NOT EAT HERE!!!!!🤬🤬
The food was ok but the place was dirty :( order takeout its better
Stopped in on a whim before work and was completely surprised with how good the food was. I'll definitely be back very soon.

Very cozy family run restaurant! The food is very tasty, the prices are good, and the staff is very nice. I would recommend the pad kee mao, the pad Thai, or the fried rice.

As others have noted, it's not as great as Thai Spice which was here before, but it's still a nice, decent neighborhood restaurant.  Those who said it has high prices and slow service must have been referring to the old place.  I was pleasantly surprised by the prices here and the portion sizes of the tasty food.

It's spicy alright! Lovely staff make you feel comfortable.  Make sure you customize your food's spicy level - less spicy should be what you go for in case you're not sure.  They post your picture on their wall if you go for high spicy foods.  Food is delicious no matter how less or more spicy it is.  I had vegetarian dish - it was pretty delicious. They don't add fish oil or eggs or chicken if you don't want them to.
Number one favorite Thai place, always! I've been going for probably 20 years! EDIT: Tony sold the place so I don’t know how the new food is, but interested to try.

So its nice they cater to different tastes, as well as honor vegetarian and vegan needs..... perhaps slightly better ingredients would make it better. Nice people, but typical horrible pop music played.... so it goes. ..

Updated 4/9/16: My prior review was for Thai Spice, the prior business at this location. Pho's Spicier Thai Cuisine is a completely different owner and has been redecorated. Service was better than with the former owner, but the food is nowhere near as good. It no longer stands out among the other Thai options in the area.  Thai Spice review: This is the best Thai I've had in Chicago. The prices are a bit high, but the quality and portion sizes make it worth it. The owner is chatty and will make small talk while your food is prepared.
Really good curry, and the lychee dessert was delish

This is a new Thai restaurant that has taken the space of Thai Spice. It is worth noting because it is definitely not the same food, although the decor is basically the same. The only positive thing about this new Thai place is the price... you can get a lot for your money. That, unfortunately, is where it ends. The food was simply not good. I ordered Pad Thai that lacked flavor, pot stickers that were dry and tasted like carrot puree, Pho that my husband literally couldn't finish, and crab rangoons that were essentially crispy wontons. Could they have been having an off day? Maybe. But I won't be back and wouldn't recommend it to anyone... Especially in this area - there are too many wonderful Thai restaurants within a few blocks of here.
(Translated by Google) The food is authentic, but the service is very slow.  (Original) la comida es autentica,  pero muy lento el servicio.

It's a very pricey place for food that wasn't that great. It comes in big portions for sure but  the slow service made the entire experience just average.
I've long had Thai Spice stand up to other folks 'best Thai in chicago' places. All other Thai restaurants in the city pale in comparison.
Delicious. Crab puffs were big and very well stuffed. Fried rice and pad khee map were on point! Only reason they lost a star is because of slow service. With that said, I will definitely be back.
Ammmmazing!!! Can't stop eating! What's not to love!
Best Thai place I have eaten at. No masking of bad cooking with sugar or color. All natural and unbelievable taste. BYOB is another benefit

Excellent food and service. This place is on the pricey side. Expect to pay about $20-25 bucks per person for a meal and a soft drink. However, the portions are very generous. You'll only be able to eat about half.
Great food, slower mom and pop service.

Thai food that will blow you away. Grab a sweet white wine because the spice levels can actually get to authentic levels without just dumping chili flakes all over your food. The papaya salad is amazing also, the Panang noodle is transcendent.

The tea and appetizer I got was also very enjoyable with attentive but not overbearing or rushing staff.

A bit off the beaten path but the Thai food is amazing. It can get pretty spicy, hence the name, so be prepared. The owner is usually there, chatting up the customers, while his wife is in the kitchen making this amazing food. The decor is basic but the space is comfortable.

Food: 9 out of 10 Service: 8 out of 10 Value: 8 out of 10  Overall: Love the ambiance of this eclectic little place. The food is definitely worth it - and listen when the owner explains the spice-level, it's important or you might get something TOO spicy.
The Panang curry is to die for. and Anthony is really nice to his customers... You're treated well. He loves Loyola kids too :)

I've tried a number of Thai places across the city, and Thai Spice is honestly the best. The owner is a nice guy who will come to your table and make conversation, the atmosphere of the place is well-decorated and very welcoming. The pad thai and pad see ew are totally great. You also get A LOT of food for the money, so don't be too put off by the already pretty reasonable price tag.

Let's start with the bad. The food is very average for Thai. Nothing too outstanding, but here comes the best part, the owner. The owner is probably the next coolest guy, right next to 2Chainz and Chief Keef. He is truly the nicest man and will start a conversation with anything.
i loved the soup! the service was slow, but very friendly and likable people. personally one of my favs, decor was great! loved how i could sit on the floor and eat, very different.
